      <div xml:id="NA66-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu maṉaimaruṭci.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is the confusion in the house.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA66">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            miḷakupey taṉaiya cuvaiya puṉkā</l>
<l>            yulaṟutalai yukāayc citarcitart tuṇṭa</l>
<l>            pulampuko ṇeṭuñciṉai yēṟi niṉaintutaṉ</l>
<l>            poṟikiḷa reruttam veṟipaṭa maṟukip</l>
<l>            puṉpuṟā vuyavum ventuka ḷiyavi </l>
<l>            ṉayanta kātalar puṇarntaṉa ḷāyiṉuñ</l>
<l>            civantoḷi maḻuṅki yamarttaṉa kollō</l>
<l>            kōtai mayaṅkiṉuṅ kuṟuntoṭi nekiḻiṉuṅ</l>
<l>            kāḻpey yalkuṟ kācumuṟai tiriyiṉu</l>
<l>            māṇalaṅ kaiyaṟak kaluḻumeṉ </l>
<l>            māyak kuṟumakaṇ malarēr kaṇṇe.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">Even if she is united with the lover she longed for</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the hot dusty way where the red(?) dove suffers,</l>
<l rend="indent2">whirling in a frenzy, its neck shining with spots,</l>
<l rend="indent2">deliberately(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">niṉaintu</term> might be taken as an adverb, and in an unusual semantic sense, but how else to make sense of it here?</note>, rising to a lonely(?) long branch,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when it had eaten<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uṇṭa</term>: actually we would expect another absolutive here, or, if this really is supposed to give the cause of the bird's strange behaviour, an abs. + <term xml:lang="ta">eṉa</term>.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">scattering bits(?) from the Ukāy tree with withered head,</l>
<l rend="indent4">the red unripe fruits that tasted as if poured with pepper,</l>
<l>– have they not been at strife, dimming in the brightness, reddening,</l>
<l>the blossom-like eyes of my charming(?) little daughter,</l>
<l rend="indent2">whose glorious beauty dims to motionlessness,</l>
<l rend="indent">even when [her] garland is confused,</l>
<l rend="indent">even when [her] small bangles become loose,</l>
<l rend="indent">even when the order of beads is twisted on [her] girdle-wearing hip?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
